The suffix "-butyl" indicates that the main carbon chain contains four carbon atoms. Finally, the suffix "-formate" indicates that there is a formate group (HCOO) attached to the rest of the molecule.

Therefore, the molecular formula of 4-ethenoxybutyl formate is C6H11O2.
